Many interesting food stalls in this Coffeeshop, Korean fried chicken by Koreans. Thai food and an impressive prata stall. The fish and chips is also very popular. The Coffeeshop can get crowded during peak hours. Becareful of the auntie serving you drinks as her maths is not so good and you May get charged extra for drinks, be sure to double check your drinks order.

This coffee shop is less busy in the weekend morning, cos only a few stalls is open for breakfast. There is minced pork noodle, Ian-Tau Sarawak Laksa.

Busy coffee shop during lunch and dinner time. Famous Waker chicken stall and Bangkok D.K. Thai Food is in the coffee shop. Come early if you want to get a seat especially during dinner time from 7pm onwards there will be snaking queue for the Korea food. This coffee shop has international food from Japanese ramen, Thai, Vietnamese, Korean and local.

Its just a regular coffeeshop but there's variety of food.

It serves:
1. Japanese ramen
2. Tze char
3. Fishball noodles
4. Chicken rice
5. Thai cuisine
6. Vietnamese cuisine
7. Korean chicken
8. Prawn noodles

Family of 3 ordered:
1. Fried seafood tang hoon
2. Olive fried rice
3. Prawn cake
4. Chicken tender fillet (sweet spicy)
5. Stir fry kai lan
6. Stir fry sambal sweet potato leaves
